title: WALLACE STATE VOLLEYBALL: No. 18 Lions close regular season with perfect ACCC mark
text:
Larger font size Posted: Thursday, October 22, 2015 7:41 pm WALLACE STATE VOLLEYBALL: No. 18 Lions close regular season with perfect ACCC mark Wallace State Media Relations cullmantimes.com 
HANCEVILLE — No. 18 Wallace State volleyball wrapped up the regular season Wednesday night at Gadsden State, finishing off a perfect 14-0 mark in Alabama Community College Conference (ACCC) play. 
Wallace State (36-6) defeated Gadsden State 27-25, 18-25, 25-20, 25-17, extending its ACCC winning streak to 28 matches. The Lions haven’t dropped an ACCC match since Oct. 2013. 
Sophomore CeCe Hall, an Alabama commit, finished with 18 kills and three blocks for Wallace State, Kheala Roberts had 11 kills and sophomore setter Alexandra Gamble contributed 38 assists. 
MaKenzie Bearden, a freshman from Geraldine, added nine kills for the Lions, Kelsea Bivins had eight digs and six kills and August Newberry tallied seven digs. 
Wallace State clinched its eighth consecutive ACCC regular season crown last week in a home victory over Faulkner State.
